1
00:00:06,875 --> 00:00:08,875
[tense music playing]

2
00:00:10,583 --> 00:00:13,208
ABUSE RAMPANT AT
CHIBA NURSING HOME

3
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:16,916
[Yamashiro] What the hell is this?

4
00:00:18,583 --> 00:00:20,000
And they have videos.

5
00:00:21,416 --> 00:00:24,000
[altered voice] <i>Hello. Mr. Udagawa.</i>

6
00:00:24,083 --> 00:00:26,333
<i>- Delicious, huh? Open your mouth.</i>
- [Udagawa] <i>No!</i>

7
00:00:26,416 --> 00:00:28,166
MR. A: (SOUNDS LIKE HE'S IN PAIN)

8
00:00:28,250 --> 00:00:30,666
<i>- Don't you dare waste it. Eat up.</i>
- [Yamashiro] This isn't good.

9
00:00:31,458 --> 00:00:33,541
The source is either
the family of that guy

10
00:00:33,625 --> 00:00:36,541
or a member of the hospital staff.

11
00:00:37,416 --> 00:00:40,875
Yamashiro, do what you have to
to make sure we don't get fined for this.

12
00:00:47,625 --> 00:00:48,791
[music fades]

13
00:00:48,875 --> 00:00:50,291
[Yamashiro sighs]

14
00:00:50,375 --> 00:00:51,750
Mr. Sugawara,

15
00:00:53,125 --> 00:00:55,416
you should know better than
to talk to me like that.

16
00:00:55,500 --> 00:00:57,791
[tense music playing]

17
00:00:57,875 --> 00:00:58,791
I'm sorry.

18
00:00:59,958 --> 00:01:00,875
I got carried away.

19
00:01:03,083 --> 00:01:06,708
Now that the media's got a hold of this,
the government's not gonna have a choice.

20
00:01:06,791 --> 00:01:09,291
They're gonna have to take action on this.

21
00:01:10,583 --> 00:01:12,958
At the very least,
they'll suspend our license.

22
00:01:13,041 --> 00:01:13,875
[Sugawara] Sir…

23
00:01:16,208 --> 00:01:18,458
You know we forced that guy Iemori

24
00:01:18,541 --> 00:01:22,250
to write out his last will
and testament over and over?

25
00:01:24,375 --> 00:01:27,416
What would happen
if a video of that got out?

26
00:01:27,500 --> 00:01:29,791
Of you forcing him to write his will?

27
00:01:30,291 --> 00:01:31,583
What'd you film that for?

28
00:01:31,666 --> 00:01:33,166
It's a hypothetical question.

29
00:01:33,250 --> 00:01:36,958
Goddamn kids with their phones.
They can't jerk off without filming it!

30
00:01:37,041 --> 00:01:38,833
No, sir, please calm down.

31
00:01:38,916 --> 00:01:40,541
Hypothetically.

32
00:01:40,625 --> 00:01:42,583
If a video like that ever got out,

33
00:01:42,666 --> 00:01:45,166
it wouldn't be just a… fine or something!

34
00:01:45,250 --> 00:01:46,333
We'd be finished!

35
00:01:47,791 --> 00:01:48,708
[sighs]

36
00:01:49,708 --> 00:01:53,750
I want… you to find out who was filming.

37
00:01:57,125 --> 00:01:58,416
I think…

38
00:02:00,500 --> 00:02:03,416
I have a pretty damn good idea
who's pulling the strings.

39
00:02:11,458 --> 00:02:13,125
Dammit, Kujo.

40
00:02:13,208 --> 00:02:14,291
- Little shit!
- [music ends]

41
00:02:14,375 --> 00:02:16,625
Ow! [groans]

42
00:02:21,041 --> 00:02:23,000
[altered voice] <i>What's the matter</i>
<i>with you, anyway?</i>

43
00:02:23,083 --> 00:02:24,208
<i>Just swallow it.</i>

44
00:02:24,291 --> 00:02:29,125
This video was on the USB you got
from Mr. Mibu the other day, huh?

45
00:02:29,208 --> 00:02:30,125
Uh-huh.

46
00:02:30,791 --> 00:02:33,583
But how'd you know
he'd be able to get his hands on it?

47
00:02:35,291 --> 00:02:37,166
I remembered someone I'd met before.

48
00:02:38,041 --> 00:02:39,041
What do you mean?

49
00:02:41,083 --> 00:02:43,916
You know, you should eat, Mr. Karasuma.

50
00:02:44,416 --> 00:02:48,375
Junk food in the morning?
What, no more fasting?

51
00:02:48,458 --> 00:02:49,416
Yeah.

52
00:02:51,125 --> 00:02:53,041
Because today's gonna be busy.

53
00:02:53,916 --> 00:02:54,750
Is it? Why's that?

54
00:02:56,291 --> 00:02:57,875
Mr. Karasuma, I wanted to ask.

55
00:02:57,958 --> 00:03:01,125
Could you contact the reporter
who wrote the news article again?

56
00:03:03,833 --> 00:03:05,833
[theme music playing]

57
00:03:31,666 --> 00:03:33,541
- [breathing heavily]
- [Sugawara] Kuga.

58
00:03:34,458 --> 00:03:36,583
Are you the one who leaked the video?

59
00:03:40,916 --> 00:03:42,875
I think very highly of you, you know?

60
00:03:45,833 --> 00:03:47,458
So I'd rather you just fess up.

61
00:03:49,458 --> 00:03:50,458
[coughs]

62
00:03:50,541 --> 00:03:51,625
I told you.

63
00:03:52,166 --> 00:03:53,333
[coughs]

64
00:03:53,416 --> 00:03:54,791
I don't know anything.

65
00:03:54,875 --> 00:03:56,041
[panting]

66
00:03:56,125 --> 00:03:57,083
But you

67
00:03:58,041 --> 00:03:59,375
didn't believe me.

68
00:04:00,291 --> 00:04:03,750
So, Mr. Sugawara, I'm at your mercy.

69
00:04:04,750 --> 00:04:06,166
Do what you want.

70
00:04:07,125 --> 00:04:09,125
[ominous music playing]

71
00:04:09,750 --> 00:04:10,875
[Sugawara] I see.

72
00:04:12,916 --> 00:04:16,625
The reason the government created
the medical system and social supports

73
00:04:17,250 --> 00:04:20,750
wasn't to save lives
or to reduce people's suffering.

74
00:04:21,625 --> 00:04:25,375
It was to keep people healthy
so they could work harder,

75
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:29,375
increasing the strength of Japan.

76
00:04:32,041 --> 00:04:34,041
[dramatic sting]

77
00:04:35,833 --> 00:04:37,916
It isn't like that today, though.

78
00:04:40,833 --> 00:04:44,791
Our numbers are out of control,
and the useless are discarded.

79
00:04:45,625 --> 00:04:46,875
[dramatic sting]

80
00:04:57,125 --> 00:04:59,625
[Kuga screaming]

81
00:04:59,708 --> 00:05:00,875
[grunts]

82
00:05:00,958 --> 00:05:02,583
[music fades]

83
00:05:11,500 --> 00:05:12,791
Hello, Mr. Kuga.

84
00:05:14,375 --> 00:05:16,708
We're from the Honjo Police Department.

85
00:05:16,791 --> 00:05:19,625
Your doctor filed a report,
so we'd like to ask you some questions.

86
00:05:19,708 --> 00:05:20,708
[Kuga groans]

87
00:05:21,541 --> 00:05:22,708
Sorry, I don't…

88
00:05:23,583 --> 00:05:26,666
I was drunk and I passed out so…
Then I woke up here like this.

89
00:05:27,666 --> 00:05:31,333
- So you don't know how you got hurt?
- No, it's just a blank, so yeah.

90
00:05:31,416 --> 00:05:32,333
[inhales sharply]

91
00:05:32,416 --> 00:05:34,291
[cop] Please contact us
if you remember anything.

92
00:05:34,375 --> 00:05:35,416
Yes, sir.

93
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:38,041
All right.

94
00:05:38,125 --> 00:05:40,666
Doctor, can you tell us more
about his injuries?

95
00:05:40,750 --> 00:05:43,125
[doctor] Absolutely. Follow me, please.

96
00:05:57,458 --> 00:06:00,541
[Kuga] <i>I figure Sugawara bugged</i>
<i>the hospital room,</i>

97
00:06:00,625 --> 00:06:02,333
<i>so I'm texting you instead.</i>

98
00:06:02,416 --> 00:06:03,750
<i>They still think it was me,</i>

99
00:06:03,833 --> 00:06:06,833
<i>but… I'm out of the woods for now.</i>

100
00:06:08,291 --> 00:06:11,166
[scoffs] <i>The article</i>
<i>about Iemori is crazy.</i>

101
00:06:11,250 --> 00:06:13,833
<i>Fuckin' Sugawara was so pissed.</i>

102
00:06:14,666 --> 00:06:15,583
[phone buzzes]

103
00:06:16,958 --> 00:06:20,541
GOOD JOB, KUGA.
HOW ARE YOU? HURT TOO BAD?

104
00:06:20,625 --> 00:06:21,750
[chuckles]

105
00:06:21,833 --> 00:06:23,708
[Kuga] <i>Hurts like hell.</i>

106
00:06:24,750 --> 00:06:25,958
[dramatic sting]

107
00:06:26,041 --> 00:06:27,166
<i>Mibu.</i>

108
00:06:28,041 --> 00:06:29,083
[chuckles]

109
00:06:30,208 --> 00:06:32,208
[upbeat music playing]

110
00:06:33,125 --> 00:06:34,125
[Yamashiro] <i>Hi. Sugawara?</i>

111
00:06:35,125 --> 00:06:36,208
[Sugawara] <i>Yeah?</i>

112
00:06:36,916 --> 00:06:39,541
Did you figure out
who leaked those videos?

113
00:06:40,125 --> 00:06:41,958
No, not yet.

114
00:06:42,041 --> 00:06:45,750
I just put my prime suspect
in the hospital and then bugged his room.

115
00:06:45,833 --> 00:06:48,125
What? You put him in the hospital?

116
00:06:48,208 --> 00:06:49,916
What's the matter with you?
Are you insane?

117
00:06:50,583 --> 00:06:53,083
<i>These videos were on the news</i>
<i>for everyone to see.</i>

118
00:06:53,833 --> 00:06:55,666
<i>The media's gonna be all over you.</i>

119
00:06:56,833 --> 00:06:58,916
Tell me about it.
There's already a swarm of them

120
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:01,500
outside the care home. It's gotten crazy.

121
00:07:01,583 --> 00:07:04,250
I can't get close to my house
or my girlfriend's either.

122
00:07:04,333 --> 00:07:06,833
[sighs] What are we gonna do?

123
00:07:07,708 --> 00:07:09,458
[Yamashiro] <i>The police have no choice.</i>

124
00:07:09,541 --> 00:07:11,500
<i>They have to investigate</i>
<i>'cause of those videos.</i>

125
00:07:12,958 --> 00:07:15,708
If they find out
that the place is being run by a thug,

126
00:07:15,791 --> 00:07:16,958
it'll make things even worse.

127
00:07:17,041 --> 00:07:19,541
What do we do about
the staff member in the videos?

128
00:07:20,125 --> 00:07:21,833
[Yamashiro] <i>If it was just him,</i>

129
00:07:21,916 --> 00:07:24,958
<i>he would just get charged with assault,</i>
<i>and that'd be it.</i>

130
00:07:25,041 --> 00:07:26,458
However,

131
00:07:27,416 --> 00:07:31,041
if they suspect the whole facility
of abusing patients, then

132
00:07:31,916 --> 00:07:33,958
even you would be in
a precarious position.

133
00:07:35,208 --> 00:07:39,541
<i>And if there's a video</i>
<i>of you forcing someone to write a will,</i>

134
00:07:39,625 --> 00:07:41,083
<i>then you're finished.</i>

135
00:07:41,833 --> 00:07:45,708
You and I would both get arrested
for fraud and breach of trust

136
00:07:45,791 --> 00:07:46,833
among other things.

137
00:07:49,125 --> 00:07:50,208
[music fades]

138
00:07:51,833 --> 00:07:53,291
[woman] Attorney Yamashiro.

139
00:07:55,083 --> 00:07:56,625
May I have a moment?

140
00:07:58,666 --> 00:08:00,625
I'm Ichida from the <i>Toei Shimbun.</i>

141
00:08:02,750 --> 00:08:07,375
You're… retained by the Kikogi Association
that runs the residence, am I right?

142
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:11,625
I have some questions for you
regarding a coerced will.

143
00:08:13,583 --> 00:08:14,583
Uh, sir!

144
00:08:15,166 --> 00:08:17,125
Could you just give us a few words?

145
00:08:17,208 --> 00:08:19,791
Goddamn reporters!
Who do you think you are?

146
00:08:19,875 --> 00:08:20,750
[growls]

147
00:08:25,083 --> 00:08:27,375
If you spread lies about me, I'll sue you.

148
00:08:28,125 --> 00:08:29,541
Are you prepared for that?

149
00:08:33,625 --> 00:08:35,166
Stop following me!

150
00:08:35,250 --> 00:08:37,791
It was a great article.
I'm glad it went viral.

151
00:08:37,875 --> 00:08:38,708
[chuckles]

152
00:08:38,791 --> 00:08:40,083
[Ichida] Thanks for the scoop.

153
00:08:40,166 --> 00:08:43,291
As soon as it hit,
all the major outlets picked it up.

154
00:08:43,875 --> 00:08:47,083
And if I post my next one
all about a big-time lawyer

155
00:08:47,166 --> 00:08:48,375
<i>aiding and abetting a gang,</i>

156
00:08:49,250 --> 00:08:51,000
<i>it'll go even more viral.</i>

157
00:08:51,083 --> 00:08:52,375
[indistinct chatter]

158
00:08:55,666 --> 00:08:58,125
[Karasuma] Ms. Ichida from <i>Toei Shimbun</i>
is very happy, Mr. Kujo.

159
00:08:58,750 --> 00:08:59,750
Is that so?

160
00:09:01,916 --> 00:09:04,375
You know, Mr. Karasuma,
you sure are well-connected.

161
00:09:04,458 --> 00:09:05,291
Huh?

162
00:09:05,375 --> 00:09:06,541
Not as well as you are, sir.

163
00:09:06,625 --> 00:09:07,916
Yeah, no.

164
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:10,416
All of my contacts are
scary-looking characters

165
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:12,250
covered in tattoos and piercings.

166
00:09:12,750 --> 00:09:14,750
[both slurping]

167
00:09:15,958 --> 00:09:18,000
Conversely, you, Mr. Karasuma,

168
00:09:18,500 --> 00:09:22,958
know very approachable people,
most of whom, I've noticed, are women.

169
00:09:23,833 --> 00:09:25,958
Hmm. Yeah, I guess that's true.

170
00:09:28,041 --> 00:09:30,416
We're both lawyers.
Why are we so different?

171
00:09:32,166 --> 00:09:33,708
[Karasuma] Mmm…

172
00:09:35,833 --> 00:09:37,666
- Our looks.
- Huh?

173
00:09:37,750 --> 00:09:39,708
[laughs] That's what you're thinking.

174
00:09:39,791 --> 00:09:41,000
[laughs]

175
00:09:41,083 --> 00:09:44,125
You… you said it, not me.

176
00:09:44,208 --> 00:09:45,166
It's just a coincidence.

177
00:09:45,250 --> 00:09:46,791
It's not a coincidence.

178
00:09:46,875 --> 00:09:50,125
Yakushimae just ignores me
whenever I ask her out.

179
00:09:50,208 --> 00:09:52,875
But she goes to that Chinese restaurant
with you all the time.

180
00:09:52,958 --> 00:09:56,666
The only time you asked her out
was for Japan's number one takoyaki.

181
00:09:56,750 --> 00:09:58,708
That doesn't count as asking someone out.

182
00:09:59,208 --> 00:10:00,083
Sure it does.

183
00:10:00,166 --> 00:10:02,958
Oh my God, how did you ever get married
with an attitude like that?

184
00:10:04,333 --> 00:10:06,375
That explains the divorce.

185
00:10:06,458 --> 00:10:08,500
[chuckles] It's written
all over your face.

186
00:10:08,583 --> 00:10:10,833
[laughs] Again, you said it, not me.

187
00:10:10,916 --> 00:10:12,791
- [door slams open]
- [Yamashiro] Hey, Kujo!

188
00:10:15,708 --> 00:10:18,291
[Kujo] I've been expecting you,
Mr. Yamashiro.

189
00:10:18,375 --> 00:10:19,916
Expecting me, huh?

190
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:21,916
[Kujo] I figured it was about time
you showed up.

191
00:10:22,500 --> 00:10:23,791
Hello. My name's Shinji Karasuma.

192
00:10:23,875 --> 00:10:24,916
Shut it!

193
00:10:25,916 --> 00:10:29,166
You used the media to try
and put me in a corner.

194
00:10:30,875 --> 00:10:32,083
You got me.

195
00:10:32,791 --> 00:10:34,625
I taught you well, Kujo.

196
00:10:34,708 --> 00:10:35,875
You got me good.

197
00:10:36,875 --> 00:10:39,166
I don't know how much evidence
you've got, but

198
00:10:40,208 --> 00:10:41,791
I'll make you a deal.

199
00:10:43,416 --> 00:10:46,291
It's not as if you enjoy
any of this, right?

200
00:10:50,750 --> 00:10:53,333
Look, I'll pay back
all of Mr. Iemori's estate.

201
00:10:54,791 --> 00:10:57,291
Okay? You win, Attorney Kujo.

202
00:11:00,541 --> 00:11:03,083
[Kujo] All right. I'll end it.
But in exchange,

203
00:11:04,750 --> 00:11:05,833
you will…

204
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:09,416
surrender your license today.

205
00:11:09,500 --> 00:11:10,541
Huh?!

206
00:11:10,625 --> 00:11:12,083
[upbeat music playing]

207
00:11:12,666 --> 00:11:14,958
You have to quit practicing law for good.

208
00:11:16,250 --> 00:11:17,666
You son of a…

209
00:11:18,166 --> 00:11:21,250
I did you a favor coming here,
and you treat me like this?

210
00:11:22,041 --> 00:11:23,583
You're telling me to quit?

211
00:11:24,458 --> 00:11:26,541
Me? I was your second father. [laughs]

212
00:11:26,625 --> 00:11:27,916
Who do you think you are?

213
00:11:29,458 --> 00:11:31,000
I'll crush you, kid.

214
00:11:31,500 --> 00:11:34,083
Have you forgotten who you're talking to?

215
00:11:37,541 --> 00:11:38,708
Maybe, yeah.

216
00:11:43,625 --> 00:11:45,708
I think I did. Why don't you remind me?

217
00:11:47,833 --> 00:11:48,916
[music ends]

218
00:11:49,500 --> 00:11:50,916
[Yamashiro] Come and get me!

219
00:11:51,625 --> 00:11:53,291
I'm not finished yet.

220
00:11:53,375 --> 00:11:54,666
[liquid pouring]

221
00:11:54,750 --> 00:11:59,125
[Yamashiro] It's stupid to think
that lawyers have any power.

222
00:11:59,208 --> 00:12:00,208
[hiccups]

223
00:12:00,291 --> 00:12:04,375
It's only ever the rich
who have any power. Am I wrong?

224
00:12:05,666 --> 00:12:07,166
It does make you wonder.

225
00:12:07,833 --> 00:12:12,833
Lawyers with any brains
only take on clients with deep pockets.

226
00:12:13,541 --> 00:12:17,083
The poor are stuck
with court-appointed lawyers.

227
00:12:17,166 --> 00:12:18,708
They don't have any choice.

228
00:12:20,208 --> 00:12:22,250
And if they get one
that doesn't give a shit,

229
00:12:22,333 --> 00:12:24,208
they end up losing
when they should've won.

230
00:12:24,916 --> 00:12:25,791
[laughs]

231
00:12:25,875 --> 00:12:28,000
We're supposed to be equal under the law.

232
00:12:28,500 --> 00:12:31,875
Obviously money turns that
into a friggin' fantasy.

233
00:12:31,958 --> 00:12:33,291
Am I right, Kujo?

234
00:12:33,375 --> 00:12:34,375
[groans]

235
00:12:35,500 --> 00:12:37,875
I charge everyone 330,000,

236
00:12:37,958 --> 00:12:40,375
regardless of whether
the client is rich or poor.

237
00:12:40,916 --> 00:12:44,916
- I don't care about social status.
- 300,000 yen?!

238
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:48,416
And I don't take a percentage
of bail either. That's my policy.

239
00:12:49,083 --> 00:12:51,708
But I'm still too expensive
for a lot of people.

240
00:12:51,791 --> 00:12:53,083
[Yamashiro] What the hell?

241
00:12:53,166 --> 00:12:54,875
You're not running a charity.

242
00:12:55,875 --> 00:13:00,375
It makes sense to charge more for the rich
in, let's say, complicated cases.

243
00:13:00,458 --> 00:13:03,458
But I've never heard of a lawyer
being such a pushover.

244
00:13:03,541 --> 00:13:05,041
It's something to think about.

245
00:13:06,583 --> 00:13:07,875
It reminds me…

246
00:13:09,750 --> 00:13:11,666
“He who fights with monsters should

247
00:13:12,750 --> 00:13:15,375
be careful lest he thereby
become a monster.”

248
00:13:17,666 --> 00:13:20,083
“And if you gaze long into an abyss,

249
00:13:20,166 --> 00:13:21,583
the abyss will also…

250
00:13:24,500 --> 00:13:26,000
gaze into you.”

251
00:13:27,041 --> 00:13:29,041
[chuckles]

252
00:13:31,333 --> 00:13:32,416
[groans]

253
00:13:33,666 --> 00:13:35,875
Nietzsche's <i>Beyond Good and Evil?</i>

254
00:13:37,583 --> 00:13:40,208
That's a pretty overused quote,
don't you think?

255
00:13:44,958 --> 00:13:46,958
[somber music playing]

256
00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:24,875
I'm grateful to you, sir,

257
00:14:25,583 --> 00:14:28,916
for everything you did for me
and everything you taught me.

258
00:14:52,750 --> 00:14:53,916
[music fades]

259
00:14:55,875 --> 00:14:59,291
[Sugawara] One of your guys filed
a complaint for assault.

260
00:15:00,125 --> 00:15:04,416
Well, that's because a video
of you beating us up went viral.

261
00:15:04,500 --> 00:15:07,208
The cops told us to file a report,
so we did.

262
00:15:07,708 --> 00:15:09,083
[Sugawara] <i>Uh-huh.</i>

263
00:15:09,166 --> 00:15:10,958
<i>Withdraw it. Now.</i>

264
00:15:11,458 --> 00:15:12,583
Sure.

265
00:15:12,666 --> 00:15:14,708
Yeah, I'll get right on that.

266
00:15:16,833 --> 00:15:20,333
You're the one behind this whole thing,
aren't you, Mibu?

267
00:15:22,500 --> 00:15:23,458
Sorry,

268
00:15:23,958 --> 00:15:25,958
I don't know what you… mean.

269
00:15:26,541 --> 00:15:27,625
Mark my words.

270
00:15:28,750 --> 00:15:31,500
One day, I'll make you pay for this.

271
00:15:32,416 --> 00:15:34,750
[Kuga sighs, chuckles]

272
00:15:35,625 --> 00:15:37,625
Did Sugawara find out about me?

273
00:15:37,708 --> 00:15:39,208
No, he didn't.

274
00:15:39,291 --> 00:15:40,833
[both laugh]

275
00:15:40,916 --> 00:15:41,958
Good.

276
00:15:42,041 --> 00:15:44,916
Ah, I wanna tell you,
you're amazing, Kuga.

277
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:47,625
You infiltrated their operation
and didn't get caught.

278
00:15:47,708 --> 00:15:50,375
[Kuga] No, you're the one
who knew exactly what to do.

279
00:15:50,916 --> 00:15:54,083
You knew if I snuck into the facility,
I'd find Sugawara's weakness.

280
00:15:54,166 --> 00:15:55,583
[Mibu] Weakness?

281
00:15:55,666 --> 00:15:57,250
That's not what I was after.

282
00:15:59,500 --> 00:16:02,208
I don't give a shit about Sugawara.

283
00:16:03,375 --> 00:16:06,333
I just used him to increase my reach,
that's all.

284
00:16:06,416 --> 00:16:07,583
[lighter clicking]

285
00:16:07,666 --> 00:16:08,833
[Kuga] Okay.

286
00:16:10,208 --> 00:16:11,375
Thanks.

287
00:16:11,458 --> 00:16:13,375
[mellow music playing]

288
00:16:13,458 --> 00:16:16,875
I was wondering…
How'd you manage to get those videos?

289
00:16:16,958 --> 00:16:18,416
Uh, well…

290
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:20,125
[phone smashes]

291
00:16:20,750 --> 00:16:23,416
[Kuga] <i>We were lucky</i>
<i>the damage didn't reach the data.</i>

292
00:16:24,833 --> 00:16:25,750
[Mibu] <i>Yeah, lucky.</i>

293
00:16:26,333 --> 00:16:30,041
Thanks to that, I got rid of Sugawara
and paid my debt to Mr. Kujo.

294
00:16:30,541 --> 00:16:31,666
[blows smoke]

295
00:16:32,541 --> 00:16:36,291
[Kuga] <i>I'm surprised</i>
<i>Mr. Kujo recognized me.</i>

296
00:16:36,958 --> 00:16:40,125
I think we only met once at your garage.

297
00:16:41,375 --> 00:16:42,875
Yeah, he's like that.

298
00:16:44,500 --> 00:16:46,125
Anyway, I owe you one, Kuga.

299
00:16:46,208 --> 00:16:47,958
Go sit in a hot spring for a while.

300
00:16:48,541 --> 00:16:50,000
Thank you.

301
00:16:50,083 --> 00:16:54,375
But seriously, Mibu, anything you need,
just give the word, and I'm there.

302
00:16:54,458 --> 00:16:55,291
Is that right?

303
00:16:55,375 --> 00:16:56,250
Yes sir.

304
00:16:58,541 --> 00:16:59,500
Well,

305
00:17:00,333 --> 00:17:03,666
how 'bout we find some time to go bowling?
What do you think?

306
00:17:03,750 --> 00:17:05,125
- [laughs]
- [chuckles]

307
00:17:05,208 --> 00:17:07,750
Come on, I just got my nose caved in.

308
00:17:07,833 --> 00:17:09,375
Give me a chance to recover.

309
00:17:11,583 --> 00:17:12,416
[music fades]

310
00:17:12,500 --> 00:17:19,416
LAND FOR SALE,
FEEL FREE TO CONTACT US

311
00:17:19,500 --> 00:17:20,458
[car door closes]

312
00:17:24,875 --> 00:17:27,583
[Ms. Iemori] Now that it's a vacant lot,
I feel better.

313
00:17:27,666 --> 00:17:29,791
The land our father left behind.

314
00:17:30,458 --> 00:17:33,833
Sorry you had to deal with all of this
when you're so busy.

315
00:17:33,916 --> 00:17:35,166
[Ms. Iemori] That's okay.

316
00:17:36,125 --> 00:17:38,458
Anyway,
that lawyer you found is really good.

317
00:17:38,541 --> 00:17:40,916
Well, we paid good money for him.
So, he better be good.

318
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:43,416
Still, it was a bargain.
His rate was super cheap.

319
00:17:43,500 --> 00:17:44,541
I was really shocked.

320
00:17:44,625 --> 00:17:47,208
He got the whole 400 million back.

321
00:17:47,291 --> 00:17:50,250
The standard cut is 10%, so 40 million.

322
00:17:50,333 --> 00:17:52,750
But he didn't even ask for half.
Only ten, right?

323
00:17:52,833 --> 00:17:55,000
That's amazing. Totally unheard of.

324
00:17:55,875 --> 00:17:56,916
[car horn beeps]

325
00:17:57,750 --> 00:17:59,291
[inaudible]

326
00:18:00,291 --> 00:18:01,666
[inaudible]

327
00:18:01,750 --> 00:18:02,708
What is it?

328
00:18:03,208 --> 00:18:04,750
[Keisuke] Oh no. I mean…

329
00:18:05,458 --> 00:18:06,833
Sorry, this is awkward.

330
00:18:07,458 --> 00:18:11,041
The 25 million you received
as an inter vivos gift from Dad…

331
00:18:11,875 --> 00:18:14,958
Can you include that in the distribution?

332
00:18:16,833 --> 00:18:19,291
[Ms. Iemori] Saeko wanted you
to ask me this, didn't she?

333
00:18:20,083 --> 00:18:21,375
Sure, whatever.

334
00:18:21,458 --> 00:18:23,750
I'm not obsessed enough with money
to fight over it.

335
00:18:24,458 --> 00:18:25,291
I'm sorry.

336
00:18:27,291 --> 00:18:28,333
I don't care.

337
00:18:29,791 --> 00:18:31,666
Now that the house is gone,

338
00:18:32,166 --> 00:18:34,750
I don't expect to have to
talk to you two anymore.

339
00:18:37,708 --> 00:18:40,291
You know, that reminds me of something.

340
00:18:40,791 --> 00:18:44,041
Dad said something to me at Mom's funeral.

341
00:18:44,541 --> 00:18:47,166
He told me that you hated him
since you were little.

342
00:18:48,791 --> 00:18:50,083
What do you mean?

343
00:18:50,166 --> 00:18:51,291
[Keisuke] You don't remember?

344
00:18:51,375 --> 00:18:54,708
You used to spend a lot of time
doing homework in the kitchen.

345
00:18:55,250 --> 00:18:57,375
[Ms. Iemori] <i>I could concentrate</i>
<i>better there.</i>

346
00:18:57,875 --> 00:19:00,291
[Keisuke] <i>That's when Mom</i>
<i>and Dad were at their worst.</i>

347
00:19:00,375 --> 00:19:01,875
[Mr. Iemori] You're still up?

348
00:19:01,958 --> 00:19:04,166
[Keisuke] <i>Dad wasn't home much.</i>

349
00:19:04,666 --> 00:19:06,333
<i>He'd stop at the bar every night.</i>

350
00:19:07,166 --> 00:19:10,041
<i>When he'd get home… drunk,</i>

351
00:19:10,125 --> 00:19:12,625
<i>you would get up and leave</i>
<i>as soon as he came in.</i>

352
00:19:12,708 --> 00:19:14,791
[poignant music playing]

353
00:19:14,875 --> 00:19:17,125
[Keisuke] <i>He said you've hated him</i>
<i>all this time.</i>

354
00:19:22,041 --> 00:19:24,708
Yeah, I was just reminded of that
for some reason.

355
00:19:25,208 --> 00:19:26,333
No offense.

356
00:19:27,416 --> 00:19:28,625
None taken.

357
00:19:30,458 --> 00:19:32,166
How much longer will this take?

358
00:19:32,250 --> 00:19:33,708
I'm coming, honey.

359
00:19:34,208 --> 00:19:37,000
Well, I'll leave the distribution to you.

360
00:19:39,333 --> 00:19:40,791
[car door opens, closes]

361
00:19:41,583 --> 00:19:43,375
That is not the reason

362
00:19:45,250 --> 00:19:47,166
that I was in the kitchen.

363
00:19:50,791 --> 00:19:52,708
[music fades]

364
00:19:52,791 --> 00:19:53,875
[door opens]

365
00:19:53,958 --> 00:19:55,541
[Yakushimae] Hi, you two.

366
00:19:57,458 --> 00:20:00,833
[humming happily]

367
00:20:00,916 --> 00:20:02,208
[Karasuma] Yakushimae?

368
00:20:03,666 --> 00:20:05,250
[Kujo] Is it Halloween?

369
00:20:05,333 --> 00:20:07,250
No, it's not a costume!

370
00:20:08,083 --> 00:20:08,958
[sighs]

371
00:20:10,416 --> 00:20:12,708
Bet you were always a big hit
with the girls.

372
00:20:12,791 --> 00:20:13,750
Never.

373
00:20:14,750 --> 00:20:16,333
So, how can I help you?

374
00:20:16,416 --> 00:20:18,833
Karasuma told me I should come over.

375
00:20:19,916 --> 00:20:23,541
Because you… wanted to go out with me. So?

376
00:20:24,250 --> 00:20:25,083
- Go out?
- Yeah.

377
00:20:25,166 --> 00:20:26,583
[Karasuma] That's what you said.

378
00:20:26,666 --> 00:20:29,666
You said that every time you ask her out,
she just ignores you.

379
00:20:29,750 --> 00:20:31,250
Really? Is that what I said?

380
00:20:31,333 --> 00:20:33,208
I don't mind going out with you.

381
00:20:33,291 --> 00:20:36,333
But… I'd like to go somewhere classy,

382
00:20:36,416 --> 00:20:38,000
like maybe counter-only sushi

383
00:20:38,083 --> 00:20:39,875
or teppanyaki
where they cook in front of you.

384
00:20:39,958 --> 00:20:43,250
Sorry. We have a lot of work left
from the Iemori case.

385
00:20:44,250 --> 00:20:45,166
Hmm?

386
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:47,375
But you already finished that case.

387
00:20:48,875 --> 00:20:50,500
A neighbor of hers said

388
00:20:51,625 --> 00:20:53,125
the house was torn down,

389
00:20:53,708 --> 00:20:56,041
and she split the inheritance
with her brother.

390
00:20:56,125 --> 00:20:57,083
All of it?

391
00:20:57,166 --> 00:20:58,291
Uh-huh.

392
00:20:58,375 --> 00:21:00,833
The neighbor told her,
“You did most of the caregiving."

393
00:21:01,625 --> 00:21:03,083
"You should've taken all of it.”

394
00:21:03,166 --> 00:21:04,208
And she said,

395
00:21:05,208 --> 00:21:06,291
"We're family."

396
00:21:08,791 --> 00:21:13,333
It seems like
she really put her family first

397
00:21:13,416 --> 00:21:15,041
until the very end, you know.

398
00:21:21,541 --> 00:21:24,000
So, have you chosen a restaurant?

399
00:21:24,083 --> 00:21:27,166
I don't wanna go anywhere
with fewer than a four-star rating.

400
00:21:27,250 --> 00:21:29,666
Maybe you can go
with Mr. Karasuma instead?

401
00:21:29,750 --> 00:21:30,583
[Yakushimae] What?

402
00:21:30,666 --> 00:21:32,291
- Where are you going?
- [Kujo] Somewhere.

403
00:21:32,375 --> 00:21:35,208
[Yakushimae] Oh, oh!
Hey! Not so fast, you crooked lawyer!

404
00:21:35,291 --> 00:21:36,833
- Treat me to dinner!
- [door closes]

405
00:21:42,666 --> 00:21:43,708
[Kujo] Ms. Iemori.

406
00:21:45,791 --> 00:21:46,916
Hello, Mr. Kujo.

407
00:21:47,416 --> 00:21:49,208
I'm sorry for calling out of the blue.

408
00:21:49,291 --> 00:21:51,458
That's okay. So, what's this about?

409
00:21:51,541 --> 00:21:53,375
I wanted to give you the receipt.

410
00:21:54,125 --> 00:21:57,250
Oh, you could've just sent it
to me in the mail.

411
00:21:57,333 --> 00:21:59,083
Yes, that's true, but…

412
00:21:59,166 --> 00:22:00,291
Here you go.

413
00:22:01,416 --> 00:22:02,375
All right.

414
00:22:02,458 --> 00:22:04,041
Thank you very much.

415
00:22:08,958 --> 00:22:09,833
[Kujo] Ms. Iemori.

416
00:22:13,708 --> 00:22:15,375
Can I ask a personal question?

417
00:22:19,708 --> 00:22:22,583
I was wondering if you regret
how it turned out?

418
00:22:23,625 --> 00:22:24,583
[laughs]

419
00:22:24,666 --> 00:22:25,916
Regret what?

420
00:22:26,791 --> 00:22:29,791
That you weren't able…
to take care of your father

421
00:22:29,875 --> 00:22:31,125
right until the end.

422
00:22:32,041 --> 00:22:33,666
[mournful music playing]

423
00:22:34,916 --> 00:22:38,125
I don't think you ever really cared
about getting the money back.

424
00:22:39,500 --> 00:22:43,041
But it was the only way you had
to try to make peace with yourself.

425
00:22:46,750 --> 00:22:48,375
According to your neighbors…

426
00:22:50,541 --> 00:22:53,208
you cared for your father
with such devotion…

427
00:22:55,375 --> 00:22:57,958
they were worried
you might just collapse one day.

428
00:23:02,583 --> 00:23:04,833
There's something my mentor
used to tell me.

429
00:23:06,666 --> 00:23:08,625
No matter how difficult things can get,

430
00:23:09,125 --> 00:23:11,291
no parent wants to burden their children.

431
00:23:12,625 --> 00:23:13,875
You can be sure of that.

432
00:23:17,125 --> 00:23:19,416
Even if your father
never said it out loud,

433
00:23:20,916 --> 00:23:23,666
I'm sure he was so very grateful to you.

434
00:23:30,541 --> 00:23:32,250
You did your best, Ms. Iemori.

435
00:23:43,125 --> 00:23:46,083
[sobbing]

436
00:23:59,166 --> 00:24:00,500
My dad…

437
00:24:03,291 --> 00:24:07,958
He put up with my selfishness
and all kinds of unfair demands

438
00:24:08,666 --> 00:24:11,000
whenever I was sad or lonely.

439
00:24:12,625 --> 00:24:18,333
He never said anything bad
about my mother even after she left us.

440
00:24:19,916 --> 00:24:21,125
Now I see…

441
00:24:23,291 --> 00:24:24,750
he was a good dad.

442
00:24:27,708 --> 00:24:28,708
[sniffs]

443
00:24:29,416 --> 00:24:30,291
And now…

444
00:24:33,208 --> 00:24:36,250
I just found out
he thought that I hated him.

445
00:24:38,625 --> 00:24:40,000
<i>But no…</i>

446
00:24:41,875 --> 00:24:43,000
<i>I waited</i>

447
00:24:43,500 --> 00:24:46,375
<i>for him every night</i>
<i>'cause I was so worried…</i>

448
00:24:46,458 --> 00:24:50,791
- [Mr. Iemori] Hanae, you're still up?
<i>- …that he wouldn't… come home.</i>

449
00:24:51,666 --> 00:24:53,416
<i>That's why I waited for him.</i>

450
00:25:05,583 --> 00:25:06,416
[sobs]

451
00:25:06,500 --> 00:25:08,625
I didn't know he thought I hated him.

452
00:25:11,333 --> 00:25:13,416
I must not have given him enough.

453
00:25:17,291 --> 00:25:21,000
And now he… Now my dad's dead.

454
00:25:25,291 --> 00:25:27,083
[sobbing]

455
00:25:42,833 --> 00:25:44,166
[music fades]

456
00:25:50,625 --> 00:25:53,750
[Karasuma] Is this the right castella?
The one you and Dad liked?

457
00:25:55,916 --> 00:25:57,875
It's okay, you know, Shinji.

458
00:25:57,958 --> 00:26:02,125
You've got a lot going on.
You don't have to come visit so often.

459
00:26:03,541 --> 00:26:04,916
[Karasuma] But I'm worried.

460
00:26:05,750 --> 00:26:06,791
Don't worry.

461
00:26:08,125 --> 00:26:10,541
I'm not likely to fall
and break a hip just yet.

462
00:26:12,833 --> 00:26:14,291
[Karasuma] That's a good sign.

463
00:26:16,333 --> 00:26:17,541
A good sign?

464
00:26:18,500 --> 00:26:20,625
That you're well enough to joke like that.

465
00:26:22,000 --> 00:26:22,958
Here.

466
00:26:33,500 --> 00:26:35,041
So? Is it good?

467
00:26:36,333 --> 00:26:37,666
It sure is.

468
00:26:39,416 --> 00:26:41,375
I know, right?

469
00:26:45,416 --> 00:26:47,250
[curtains sliding]

470
00:26:49,916 --> 00:26:50,916
[window unlatching]

471
00:26:52,041 --> 00:26:53,125
Hey, please don't open it.

472
00:26:53,208 --> 00:26:54,666
You should let some air in.

473
00:26:54,750 --> 00:26:57,083
If you open the window,
people outside will hear us.

474
00:26:57,166 --> 00:26:58,041
No, they won't.

475
00:26:58,125 --> 00:27:00,083
[Mrs. Karasuma] Just close it. Please.

476
00:27:01,125 --> 00:27:04,875
Okay. Right away, ma'am. There.

477
00:27:04,958 --> 00:27:06,166
Done.

478
00:27:08,541 --> 00:27:09,833
[sighs]

479
00:27:09,916 --> 00:27:10,916
But you know, Mom,

480
00:27:11,500 --> 00:27:13,208
Dad wasn't the only victim here.

481
00:27:15,083 --> 00:27:16,458
You and I are too.

482
00:27:18,291 --> 00:27:21,125
So, we don't have to live
like we did something wrong.

483
00:27:22,916 --> 00:27:24,666
It's not too late, you know,

484
00:27:25,833 --> 00:27:27,291
for us to start over.

485
00:27:30,458 --> 00:27:31,291
Okay?

486
00:27:34,291 --> 00:27:35,375
I don't know if I can.

487
00:27:35,458 --> 00:27:36,666
Sure you can.

488
00:27:39,250 --> 00:27:40,833
You can do anything.

489
00:27:44,500 --> 00:27:45,541
[sighs softly]

490
00:27:45,625 --> 00:27:46,625
Mm-hmm.

491
00:27:47,208 --> 00:27:48,166
[chuckles]

492
00:27:50,166 --> 00:27:51,250
[sighs]

493
00:27:53,833 --> 00:27:55,041
Lie down.

494
00:27:57,458 --> 00:27:58,666
Okay.

495
00:28:01,458 --> 00:28:02,875
You're so good.

496
00:28:03,750 --> 00:28:07,333
- Mr. Kujo. Mr. Mibu's here to see you.
- Oh.

497
00:28:07,416 --> 00:28:09,416
[upbeat music playing]

498
00:28:11,083 --> 00:28:14,625
Hello, sir. I finally found someone
to take the dog off your hands.

499
00:28:15,666 --> 00:28:18,666
[Karasuma] Good. Now the office
won't get torn apart anymore.

500
00:28:21,625 --> 00:28:22,791
Hey, uh, Mibu?

501
00:28:23,500 --> 00:28:24,416
[Mibu] Yeah?

502
00:28:27,500 --> 00:28:32,000
Would it be okay if I became
Black Thunder's new owner?

503
00:28:33,291 --> 00:28:34,791
You telling me you wanna keep her?

504
00:28:36,666 --> 00:28:39,625
Well, she's already
kind of like family to me.

505
00:28:45,375 --> 00:28:46,208
[Mibu] Sir…

506
00:28:48,500 --> 00:28:53,500
You know, having a dog…
means being responsible for a life.

507
00:28:54,208 --> 00:28:55,541
Do you understand?

508
00:28:56,625 --> 00:28:57,625
I understand.

509
00:28:58,125 --> 00:28:59,666
Do you really understand?

510
00:29:00,958 --> 00:29:04,625
You have to walk her every day and pick up
after her. You know, she might bite you?

511
00:29:04,708 --> 00:29:06,916
And you have to brush her
and brush her teeth. It's a lot.

512
00:29:08,041 --> 00:29:11,625
I know how much you still miss
your dog Omochi. I really get it.

513
00:29:11,708 --> 00:29:13,708
[cell phone rings]

514
00:29:13,791 --> 00:29:15,791
[music fades]

515
00:29:17,666 --> 00:29:18,500
Excuse me.

516
00:29:21,000 --> 00:29:21,958
Hello?

517
00:29:22,958 --> 00:29:23,875
Yeah.

518
00:29:27,083 --> 00:29:28,666
Who's Omochi again?

519
00:29:28,750 --> 00:29:29,791
Uh…

520
00:29:29,875 --> 00:29:31,958
His dog, who unfortunately passed away.

521
00:29:32,041 --> 00:29:35,041
So that's why he's so different
when it comes to dogs.

522
00:29:35,125 --> 00:29:36,208
Yeah.

523
00:29:36,291 --> 00:29:38,541
But he's right though.
A dog is a lot of work.

524
00:29:39,125 --> 00:29:41,250
What if you have to go away on business?

525
00:29:43,458 --> 00:29:44,833
In that case…

526
00:29:45,875 --> 00:29:47,958
- I guess you'll have to take care of her.
- [groans]

527
00:29:48,041 --> 00:29:52,083
[chuckles] Yeah.
I mean, why not, huh? We're both single.

528
00:29:52,166 --> 00:29:54,250
We're practically family.

529
00:29:54,333 --> 00:29:57,583
Well, who's to say
I'm gonna stick around here forever?

530
00:29:58,750 --> 00:30:01,750
[Mibu] Mr. Kujo,
I need your help with something.

531
00:30:03,458 --> 00:30:05,708
A guy who's helped me out in the past

532
00:30:07,166 --> 00:30:08,416
just got pinched.

533
00:30:09,083 --> 00:30:11,500
So, he needs a lawyer?
Is he a friend of yours?

534
00:30:12,958 --> 00:30:14,916
A Fushimi-gumi boss, actually.

535
00:30:15,625 --> 00:30:16,916
Kiyoshi Kyogoku.

536
00:30:17,666 --> 00:30:19,666
[tense music playing]

537
00:30:24,583 --> 00:30:25,875
[cell door slams]

538
00:30:32,166 --> 00:30:33,375
Finally.

539
00:30:34,625 --> 00:30:36,875
This doesn't make any sense at all.

540
00:30:36,958 --> 00:30:40,416
I'm the one
who almost got my watch stolen.

541
00:30:41,166 --> 00:30:42,958
So why did I get arrested?

542
00:30:44,125 --> 00:30:45,166
[Karasuma] On our way here,

543
00:30:45,250 --> 00:30:48,333
we asked the arresting officer
to explain the charges.

544
00:30:49,333 --> 00:30:52,375
According to them,
you were approached by a Kenichi Sakuma.

545
00:30:53,625 --> 00:30:54,750
[grunts]

546
00:30:54,833 --> 00:30:56,916
[Karasuma] <i>While it's true</i>
<i>that he ran toward you,</i>

547
00:30:57,000 --> 00:30:58,541
<i>he didn't intend to steal from you…</i>

548
00:30:58,625 --> 00:30:59,583
[Sakuma] What the hell?

549
00:30:59,666 --> 00:31:02,166
<i>…nevertheless,</i>
<i>you inflicted serious injury on him.</i>

550
00:31:02,666 --> 00:31:04,958
While the bodyguards were
the ones who acted,

551
00:31:05,708 --> 00:31:07,916
you are also held liable
as their employer.

552
00:31:08,000 --> 00:31:10,916
As a result, you've been charged
with assault, Mr. Kyogoku.

553
00:31:11,625 --> 00:31:14,083
But it was a robbery.
I was protecting myself.

554
00:31:14,166 --> 00:31:15,875
You're a yakuza leader, Mr. Kyogoku,

555
00:31:15,958 --> 00:31:18,666
so this is likely an excuse
to arrest and question you.

556
00:31:19,333 --> 00:31:22,458
I understand you want to settle this
and secure your release quickly.

557
00:31:22,958 --> 00:31:23,916
The victim won't agree.

558
00:31:26,041 --> 00:31:28,041
The yakuza are being underestimated.

559
00:31:28,125 --> 00:31:30,875
I saw the footage from the security camera
at the parking lot.

560
00:31:30,958 --> 00:31:34,416
I believe your bodyguards will be found
to have acted in self-defense.

561
00:31:34,916 --> 00:31:36,708
You won't be prosecuted for this.

562
00:31:36,791 --> 00:31:41,000
I heard you got some thug out
after only 20 days, so I asked for you.

563
00:31:41,500 --> 00:31:43,500
I need you to get me out of here.

564
00:31:44,000 --> 00:31:46,125
How quickly this goes depends on you.

565
00:31:46,208 --> 00:31:47,458
That's it.

566
00:31:48,625 --> 00:31:50,791
I need your phone.
I better get my guys on.

567
00:31:50,875 --> 00:31:54,416
You can't. That would go against
the purpose of this meeting.

568
00:31:55,125 --> 00:31:57,375
Lawyers have been disciplined
for doing less.

569
00:31:57,458 --> 00:31:59,583
[Kyogoku] Don't give me that bullshit.

570
00:31:59,666 --> 00:32:02,458
Fine. Give Mibu a message, then.

571
00:32:02,958 --> 00:32:04,541
You're just courier pigeons,

572
00:32:05,625 --> 00:32:06,458
aren't you?

573
00:32:06,541 --> 00:32:07,583
[music fades]

574
00:32:08,791 --> 00:32:11,750
If you want a messenger,
you can go get a new lawyer.

575
00:32:12,791 --> 00:32:14,375
All the money in the world

576
00:32:15,000 --> 00:32:17,750
doesn't make a difference
in the face of the law.

577
00:32:20,708 --> 00:32:22,708
[tense upbeat music playing]

578
00:32:22,791 --> 00:32:25,208
[whimpering]

579
00:32:28,041 --> 00:32:29,708
- Sakuma.
- Yes?

580
00:32:30,750 --> 00:32:31,958
Do you know who I am?

581
00:32:32,791 --> 00:32:34,708
Yeah, of course. Mibu.

582
00:32:36,166 --> 00:32:37,083
Then

583
00:32:38,000 --> 00:32:40,041
you must know how this world works?

584
00:32:41,041 --> 00:32:43,291
The… This world?

585
00:32:45,500 --> 00:32:48,375
[whimpering]

586
00:32:48,458 --> 00:32:49,500
Listen.

587
00:32:53,583 --> 00:32:56,708
I'm afraid you stepped in shit
that you shouldn't have stepped in.

588
00:33:01,000 --> 00:33:02,791
Withdraw the report you filed.

589
00:33:03,958 --> 00:33:05,750
[Sakuma stammering] Yes, sir.

590
00:33:06,625 --> 00:33:08,833
[music fades]

591
00:33:08,916 --> 00:33:09,958
You said

592
00:33:10,750 --> 00:33:12,791
you don't judge your clients
based on status

593
00:33:12,875 --> 00:33:14,625
or whether or not they're good people.

594
00:33:16,250 --> 00:33:18,083
Mr. Kyogoku is dangerous.

595
00:33:21,083 --> 00:33:23,750
It won't end with you
just losing your license.

596
00:33:26,416 --> 00:33:27,583
One day,

597
00:33:28,375 --> 00:33:29,875
you could lose your life.

598
00:33:31,750 --> 00:33:33,750
[siren wailing in the distance]

599
00:33:36,916 --> 00:33:38,875
[indistinct chatter]

600
00:33:38,958 --> 00:33:41,291
- Good morning Mr. Kyogoku.
- Morning. I'll stop by again soon.

601
00:33:41,375 --> 00:33:42,958
Thank you, sir. Looking forward to it.

602
00:33:43,041 --> 00:33:44,916
- Good morning!
- Good morning.

603
00:33:45,000 --> 00:33:47,291
- [man] Morning, sir.
- Hello there. It's been a while.

604
00:33:48,500 --> 00:33:49,958
You're popular here.

605
00:33:50,041 --> 00:33:53,083
[exhales] It's my wallet that they like.

606
00:33:53,166 --> 00:33:54,541
So, listen.

607
00:33:55,583 --> 00:33:59,375
I wanted to talk to you about
that lawyer of yours. He's interesting.

608
00:33:59,458 --> 00:34:00,333
[Mibu] Oh yeah?

609
00:34:00,416 --> 00:34:03,166
Yeah. Why didn't you introduce us earlier?

610
00:34:04,583 --> 00:34:07,541
I don't appreciate you hogging
a lawyer that quick on his feet.

611
00:34:08,083 --> 00:34:10,333
I felt like it would be presumptuous of me

612
00:34:10,416 --> 00:34:13,500
since the Fushimi-gumi
already have a lawyer.

613
00:34:16,666 --> 00:34:19,916
Yes, but the problem is
our lawyer lent me his phone

614
00:34:20,000 --> 00:34:21,583
without a second thought.

615
00:34:21,666 --> 00:34:24,958
Mr. Kujo, on the other hand…

616
00:34:25,750 --> 00:34:26,958
[Kujo] <i>Mr. Kyogoku.</i>

617
00:34:27,041 --> 00:34:30,041
You're aware that the police
regularly check the call history

618
00:34:30,125 --> 00:34:32,000
of known yakuza members, right?

619
00:34:33,208 --> 00:34:35,500
If I were to let you use my cell phone,

620
00:34:35,583 --> 00:34:38,250
it'd be a disadvantage not just for me,
but for you too.

621
00:34:40,750 --> 00:34:42,666
Even if the other party
doesn't agree to settle,

622
00:34:42,750 --> 00:34:45,333
I think we can
successfully argue self-defense.

623
00:34:46,083 --> 00:34:50,708
If you and your bodyguards remain silent,
in 20 days, you'll all be cut loose.

624
00:34:52,250 --> 00:34:55,291
[Kyogoku] As it turned out,
that little punk agreed to settle

625
00:34:55,375 --> 00:34:56,833
before the 20 days were up.

626
00:34:59,833 --> 00:35:00,708
[sighs]

627
00:35:00,791 --> 00:35:02,791
You know, Mibu… [smacks lips]

628
00:35:03,666 --> 00:35:05,583
Something's bothering me.

629
00:35:08,375 --> 00:35:10,500
This was the first time I've ever been

630
00:35:11,000 --> 00:35:13,625
the target of a snatch-and-grab
in this city.

631
00:35:15,291 --> 00:35:16,458
And you know what I think?

632
00:35:17,041 --> 00:35:22,083
I think that someone out there
is maybe looking to frame me.

633
00:35:31,166 --> 00:35:32,791
Pretty paranoid, huh?

634
00:35:32,875 --> 00:35:33,833
[chuckles]

635
00:35:36,083 --> 00:35:37,875
What do you say, Mibu?

636
00:35:48,750 --> 00:35:51,458
Well? Was it you?

637
00:35:52,583 --> 00:35:54,791
[dramatic music playing]

638
00:35:56,416 --> 00:35:58,875
You haven't forgotten
how sideways things can get?

639
00:36:01,458 --> 00:36:02,333
[groaning]

640
00:36:05,708 --> 00:36:07,125
[Kyogoku] Mibu…

641
00:36:08,750 --> 00:36:13,041
I'm afraid… you guys screwed
with someone you shouldn't have.

642
00:36:15,916 --> 00:36:19,208
You stole proceeds from one
of the gambling dens we look after.

643
00:36:19,291 --> 00:36:20,416
Are you crazy?

644
00:36:22,000 --> 00:36:23,666
[Mibu groans]

645
00:36:23,750 --> 00:36:26,583
The guy we caught first
ratted you out right away.

646
00:36:26,666 --> 00:36:28,250
Said it was all your idea.

647
00:36:30,083 --> 00:36:32,583
Thugs have no loyalty to their superiors.

648
00:36:33,416 --> 00:36:34,625
[Mibu groans]

649
00:36:37,166 --> 00:36:38,958
Yakuza don't rat out their superiors.

650
00:36:41,000 --> 00:36:44,916
But we all…
look out for number one, right?

651
00:36:46,166 --> 00:36:48,291
The search for love is
a search for ourselves.

652
00:36:50,750 --> 00:36:51,791
[sighs]

653
00:36:52,458 --> 00:36:56,541
You know, this heater is used
to dry the paint on cars.

654
00:36:57,416 --> 00:37:00,500
If you get too close to it,
your blood'll boil, and you'll die.

655
00:37:00,583 --> 00:37:02,083
It's pretty dangerous.

656
00:37:02,916 --> 00:37:04,250
[heater creaks loudly]

657
00:37:04,333 --> 00:37:05,958
[grunts, groans]

658
00:37:07,500 --> 00:37:10,291
Are you okay, Mibu?

659
00:37:11,250 --> 00:37:12,208
Is it hot?

660
00:37:13,750 --> 00:37:15,750
[groans]

661
00:37:17,041 --> 00:37:20,916
Don't worry.
You're too valuable to die like this.

662
00:37:21,666 --> 00:37:23,041
You know what we're gonna do?

663
00:37:23,125 --> 00:37:24,833
If you show your loyalty,

664
00:37:25,791 --> 00:37:27,000
I'll let you live.

665
00:37:27,583 --> 00:37:28,625
What do you say?

666
00:37:29,583 --> 00:37:31,375
[groans]

667
00:37:31,458 --> 00:37:32,500
I'm sorry.

668
00:37:32,583 --> 00:37:34,375
[groans]

669
00:37:34,458 --> 00:37:35,541
I'll do anything.

670
00:37:35,625 --> 00:37:38,041
Okay. Show me your loyalty.

671
00:37:38,125 --> 00:37:39,291
[groans]

672
00:37:39,375 --> 00:37:42,666
Your dog, what's its name again?
Huh? What is it?

673
00:37:42,750 --> 00:37:45,333
Omochi! Don't touch him! No!

674
00:37:45,416 --> 00:37:47,250
Oh, Omochi!

675
00:37:47,333 --> 00:37:50,333
Omochi, the dog you've had
since you were a little kid.

676
00:37:50,416 --> 00:37:51,958
- No!
- Yeah…

677
00:37:52,041 --> 00:37:54,041
[struggling]

678
00:37:55,375 --> 00:37:57,333
I want you to kill it.

679
00:37:57,416 --> 00:37:59,416
[dramatic sting]

680
00:38:00,000 --> 00:38:01,791
There's no way! I can't do that!

681
00:38:02,291 --> 00:38:04,291
[grunting]

682
00:38:05,666 --> 00:38:07,000
Ah, then you'll

683
00:38:08,125 --> 00:38:09,291
die.

684
00:38:09,375 --> 00:38:12,333
[Mibu screaming]

685
00:38:23,708 --> 00:38:25,708
[music fades]

686
00:38:28,375 --> 00:38:29,750
[dog groans]

687
00:38:39,083 --> 00:38:40,583
- [bang]
- [Omochi whimpering]

688
00:38:44,458 --> 00:38:46,458
[ominous music playing]

689
00:38:49,416 --> 00:38:50,625
Mibu.

690
00:38:51,916 --> 00:38:54,250
Remember, you chose to kill it.

691
00:38:56,041 --> 00:38:57,833
If you'd done it on my orders,

692
00:38:59,041 --> 00:39:01,791
you would've held a grudge against me,
and we can't have that.

693
00:39:10,250 --> 00:39:12,625
<i>This way, the guilt is yours to bear.</i>

694
00:39:18,500 --> 00:39:20,625
[music builds, ends]

695
00:39:24,250 --> 00:39:26,833
[indistinct chatter]

696
00:39:35,791 --> 00:39:36,958
[Kujo] Are you all right?

697
00:39:38,958 --> 00:39:40,166
Yeah, why?

698
00:39:48,583 --> 00:39:50,291
I'm Mr. Kujo. I'm an attorney.

699
00:39:52,958 --> 00:39:54,958
Please get in touch if you ever need to.

700
00:39:57,291 --> 00:39:59,375
[closing theme song playing]

701
00:42:35,291 --> 00:42:36,375
[music fades]
